ground_truth: Neff walks in past the night watchman without answering and heads towards the elevator. The night watchman looks after. Neff relocks the door and follows him to the elevator. Neff enters the elevator appearing pale and haggard with pain but maintains a deadpan expression as the night watchman joins him. The night watchman pulls the lever. the doors close and the elevator rises. The door opens to reveal a small dark reception room with a pair of frosted glass doors labeled PACIFIC ALLRISK INSURANCE COMPANY  FOUNDED 1906  MAIN OFFICE. with a little light beyond the glass doors Neff straightens up and walks heavily out of the elevator crosses the reception room to the doors and pushes them open. These lead to a balcony that runs all the way around overlooking the eleventh floor below which is filled with desks typewriters filing cabinets and business machines. Neff enters the area from the reception room while the twelfth floor remains dark. and some light shines up from the eleventh floor where two colored women are cleaning the offices — one is drymopping the floor the other moving chairs back into position. Neff moves away from the railing with a faint smile on his face and walks past two or three offices towards a glass door labeled with the number twentyseven and the names.
